value.value: Fracture or fragmentation at the lateral portion of the metaphysis of a long bone. The radiographic appearance is that of a small corner of metaphysis separated from the metaphyseal edge by thin linear radiolucency. This feature can be observed in child abuse but fragmented appearance of the metaphysis or facture-like lesions can also be detected in the setting of certain skeletal dysplasias.

Uzun bir kemiğin metafizinin yan kısmında kırık veya parçalanma. Metafizin küçük bir köşesinin metafizik kenardan ince doğrusal radyolüsansla ayrılması, radyografik görünümdür. Bu özellik, çocuk istismarında gözlenebilir; ancak, metafizin parçalanmış görüntüsü ya da facture benzeri lezyonlar, belirli iskelet displazilerinin oluşumunda da tespit edilebilir

value.value: Zlomenina nebo fragmentace boční části metafýzy dlouhé kosti. Radiograficky je patrné, že malý malý roh metafýzy je oddělený od metafyzálního okraje tenkou lineární radiolucencí. definition.value: A corner fracture is a subepiphyseal planer fracture through immature metaphyseal bone. The appearance of a corner, avulsion or bucket handle depends on the extent of bone failure and radiographic projection. Bone can fail in this pattern from both shearing and tensile stresses. The weakest area of bone for a given loading condition determines the injury threshold for that structure.
